<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880314-0062 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Blount Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BLTA POWR </CO><IN> CON UTI </IN><TEXT>   Blount Inc. said it won contracts to build three power plants, with a combined value of $270 million.    The Montgomery, Ala.-based manufacturing and construction concern will handle engineering, procurement and construction for a $100 million solar energy generator to be built in Kramer Junction, Calif. The owner will be Luz Partners VI, a developer and operator of solar power facilites.    Blount will build two facilities to be owned by subsidiaries of Environmental Power Corp., a developer and operator of electrical generating facilities: a $105 million cogeneration plant in Scrubgrass Township, Pa.; and a $65 million cogeneration plant in Sunnyside, Utah. </TEXT></DOC>